erfacing with executive leadership within Praesidiad, and is also hands-on, working closely with the field-based team, ensuring that Projects Delivers on-time, on budget and as per quality requirements – with a strong focus on financial objectives and exceeding customer satisfaction.KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:Project Leadership &amp; GovernanceLead the full lifecycle delivery of assigned Projects and Workstreams, ensuring all components are executed to comply with defined technical, commercial, and contractual standards.Define and implement Project Governance frameworks covering scope control, milestone tracking, performance reporting, and risk mitigation.Establish and manage Project KPIs, performance dashboards, and internal/external reporting mechanisms for executive stakeholders.Team &amp; Operational OversightDirect and mentor a multidisciplinary team including Project Engineers, Product Managers and Technicians for deployment, support, and commissioning.Align regional engineering, supply chain, and operations resources to meet project milestones and service expectations.Foster a high-performance culture focused on delivery quality, customer satisfaction, safety, and continuous improvement.Contract &amp; Commercial ManagementOwn the delivery and compliance of Project-level contractual obligations, including change orders, service-level agreements, and financial milestones.Manage Project budget, cost controls, and forecasting in alignment with regional financial targets.Lead resolution of contract-related issues, claims, and escalations in collaboration with Legal and Commercial teams.Customer Engagement &amp; SuccessServe as the senior operational interface with Customers. Mainly, General Contractor/Installer and Prime Contractor, as well as the end user, ensuring transparency, accountability, and trust.Monitor and enhance customer satisfaction through proactive communication, service quality, and collaborative issue resolution.Translate client needs into operational 