Supportive environment*: Join a young, energetic team with approachable leadership that values your input and fosters collaboration.\n* *Global exposure*: Work in the vibrant Dubai real estate market and engage with international clients and developers.\n\n*What We’re Looking For*\n\nWe’re searching for a proactive professional with:\n\n* Proven track record in real estate sales.\n* In‑depth knowledge of the *Dubai real estate market* and its key trends.\n* Exceptional communication and negotiation skills — you know how to build trust and close deals.\n* A relentless drive to achieve and exceed targets.\n* Strong organizational skills and ability to manage large volumes of information efficiently.\n\n*Your Key Responsibilities*\n\nAs a Broker/Sales Manager, you’ll play a pivotal role in driving our success:\n\n* Manage client relationships using CRM, ensuring seamless communication and follow‑up.\n* Participate in team meetings and strategy sessions to align on goals and share insights.\n* Attend training sessions (often via Zoom) to stay updated on new projects and developer offerings.\n* Conduct virtual presentations and schedule property viewings to guide clients through their buying journey.\n* Build and maintain strong partnerships with developers and industry stakeholders.\n* Keep our project database current by adding new listings and updating property details.\n* Create compelling client presentations using AI tools to showcase opportunities effectively.\n* Collaborate on social media content, including webinars, videos, and broker tour footage, to enhance our brand presence.\n\n*Ready to Take the Next Step?*\n\nIf you’re excited about joining a forward‑thinking team in the dynamic world of Dubai real estate, we want to hear from you! Submit your resume and a brief cover letter highlighting your relevant experience and why you’d be a great fit for this role.\n\n*Let’s build success together!*\n\nJob Type: Full-time"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2213084a4e114e43","title":"QA Lead - 100% remote","company":"Tether Operations Limited","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"a month ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2213084a4e114e43","description":"Join Tether and Shape the Future of Digital Finance\n\nAt Tether, we’re not just building products, we’re pioneering a global financial revolution. Our cutting-edge solutions empower businesses—from exchanges and wallets to payment processors and ATMs—to seamlessly integrate reserve-backed tokens across blockchains. By harnessing the power of blockchain technology, Tether enables you to store, send, and receive digital tokens instantly, securely, and globally, all at a fraction of the cost. Transparency is the bedrock of everything we do, ensuring trust in every transaction.\n\nInnovate with Tether\n\nTether Finance: Our innovative product suite features the world’s most trusted stablecoin, USDT, relied upon by hundreds of millions worldwide, alongside pioneering digital asset tokenization services.\n\nBut that’s just the beginning:\n\nTether Power: Driving sustainable growth, our energy solutions optimize excess power for Bitcoin mining using eco-friendly practices in state-of-the-art, geo-diverse facilities.\n\nTether Data: Fueling breakthroughs in AI and peer-to-peer technology, we reduce infrastructure costs and enhance global communications with cutting-edge solutions like KEET, our flagship app that redefines secure and private data sharing.\n\nTether Education: Democratizing access to top-tier digital learning, we empower individuals to thrive in the digital and gig economies, driving global growth and opportunity.\n\nTether Evolution: At the intersection of technology and human potential, we are pushing the boundaries of what is possible, crafting a future where innovation and human capabilities merge in powerful, unprecedented ways.\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nOur team is a global talent powerhouse, working remotely from every corner of the world. If you’re passionate about making a mark in the fintech space, this is your opportunity to collaborate with some of the brightest minds, pushing boundaries and setting new standards. We’ve grown fast, stayed lean, and secured our place as a leader in the industry.\n\nIf you have excellent English communication skills and are ready to contribute to the most innovative platform on the planet, Tether is the place for you.\n\nAre you ready to be part of the future?\n\nAbout the job\n\nThe goal of a QA Lead is to drive the overall quality strategy and ensure that products meet the highest standards of reliability, performance, and user satisfaction. This role combines technical expertise with leadership, guiding QA Engineers in both manual and automated testing practices while fostering a culture of quality across the organization.\n\nA QA Lead defines test strategies, plans, and processes; ensures alignment with development and product goals; and oversees the execution of testing activities throughout the release cycle. They establish and maintain automation frameworks, metrics, and reporting systems to provide visibility into quality trends and release readiness.\n\nFocused on prevention rather than detection, the QA Lead collaborates closely with cross-functional teams to integrate quality early in the development lifecycle, optimize testing efficiency, and continuously improve QA processes, tooling, and standards. Ultimately, the QA Lead ensures that every release is predictable, traceable, and confidently delivered to users.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nDefine and Drive QA Strategy: Establish and continuously refine the overall QA vision, goals, and strategy to align with product and engineering objectives, balancing manual and automated testing approaches.\nPlan and Manage Testing Activities: Oversee test planning, prioritization, and execution across projects. Ensure test coverage aligns with business impact, release timelines, and risk assessment.\nMentor and Guide QA Engineers: Provide technical and procedural guidance to QA Engineers, fostering skill development in both manual and automation testing. Conduct regular reviews and coaching sessions.\nEnsure Quality Governance and Standards: Define QA processes, templates, and best practices to standardize testing across teams. Maintain consistency in documentation, defect management, and reporting.\nCollaborate with Cross-Functional Teams: Work closely with product managers, developers, and DevOps to ensure quality is embedded throughout the SDLC. Participate in planning and other ceremonies where applicable to provide support and guidance.\nOversee Test Automation Strategy: Guide the design, maintenance, and optimization of automation frameworks. Ensure automation coverage is effective, scalable, and well-integrated into CI/CD pipelines.\nManage Test Environments and Data: Coordinate environment setup, data preparation, and version control to ensure test consistency and reliability across manual and automated executions.\nMonitor and Report on Quality Metrics: Define and track key QA KPIs (e.g., defect density, test coverage, pass rate, release readiness). Use insights to drive continuous improvement.\nFacilitate Release Readiness and Risk Assessment: Lead go/no-go decisions based on test outcomes, quality metrics, and known issues. Communicate quality status and risks clearly to stakeholders.\nDrive Continuous Improvement: Evaluate tools, processes, and team performance to identify opportunities for efficiency and quality enhancement. Champion a culture of learning and proactive defect prevention.\n\nMandatory\n\nEducation: Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, or a related field (or equivalent practical experience).\nExperience:\n5+ years of experience in Quality Assurance, including both manual and automation testing.\n3+ years of proven experience leading QA teams or managing QA processes across multiple projects.\nDemonstrated experience defining and executing QA strategies for complex software systems.\n3+ years of experience in JavaScript, Typescript & NodeJS\n3+ years of experience in test automation design and implementation (e.g., using Selenium, Cypress, Playwright, or equivalent).\n3+ years of experience in native mobile test automation design and implementation (e.g. Appium, Espresso, XCUITest, Detox, AWS Device Farm, BrowserStack App Automate, Firebase Test Lab, Sauce Labs, Kobiton, Robot Framework, BitBar, LambdaTest Mobile, HeadSpin, Fastlane, Tricentis Testim or equivalent)\nTechnical Knowledge:\nStrong understanding of QA methodologies, test design techniques, and SDLC/Agile/Scrum practices.\nProficiency in one or more programming/scripting languages (e.g., JavaScript, Python, Java, C#).\nHands-on experience with CI/CD pipelines and DevOps practices (e.g., GitHub Actions, Jenkins, GitLab CI).\nProven experience integrating automated tests into build and deployment workflows.\nKnowledge of performance, load, and security testing principles.\nProficiency in QA and defect tracking tools (e.g., Qase, TestRail, Jira, Asana, Confluence).\nLeadership & Strategy:\nProven experience in leading the design and execution of QA strategies across multiple projects.\nExpertise in defining and implementing test plans, automation frameworks, and quality metrics.\nStrong collaborative skills to align testing efforts with development, DevOps, and product management.\nAbility to critically evaluate requirements and proposals for quality, ensuring clarity, testability, and completeness.\nProficiency in monitoring and reporting on quality KPIs, defect trends, and test coverage metrics.\nExperience driving automation adoption and optimizing CI/CD pipelines for quality integration.\nDemonstrated ability to act as a “red team” for quality — identifying risks and raising no-go flags when release criteria are not met.\nProject Management Skills:\nStrong proficiency in planning, scheduling, prioritizing, and coordinating testing activities across teams.\nExperience managing distributed QA teams and collaborating across global time zones.\nAbility to balance speed, quality, and scope in fast-paced product development environments.\nSoft Skills:\nGood leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills.\nStrong analytical and problem-solving abilities.\nProven mentorship experience — guiding QA Engineers in both manual and automation domains.\nAbility to influence and advocate for quality-first principles across all stages of software delivery.\nLanguage: Proficiency in English (spoken and written).\n\nPreferred\n\nCertifications: ISTQB Advanced Level, Certified ScrumMaster (CSM), or equivalent QA leadership certification.\nTechnical Knowledge:\nExperience with cloud environments and containerization (e.g., AWS, Docker, Kubernetes).\nKnowledge of database systems (SQL, NoSQL) and API testing tools (e.g., Postman, Newman, REST Assured).\nUnderstanding of system architecture and software integration testing.\nFamiliarity with performance testing tools (e.g., JMeter, k6, Gatling).\nUnderstanding of cybersecurity principles and secure software testing practices.\nExperience with test data management and environment configuration.\nProject Management Skills:\nAbility to lead multiple QA projects concurrently with clear ownership and accountability.\nProven ability to establish QA roadmaps and continuous improvement initiatives.\n\nImportant information for candidates\nRecruitment scams have become increasingly common. To protect yourself, please keep the following in mind when applying for roles:\n\nApply only through our official channels. We do not use third-party platforms or agencies for recruitment unless clearly stated. All open roles are listed on our official careers page: https://tether.recruitee.com/\nVerify the recruiter’s identity. All our recruiters have verified LinkedIn profiles. If you’re unsure, you can confirm their identity by checking their profile or contacting us through our website.\nBe cautious of unusual communication methods. We do not conduct interviews over WhatsApp, Telegram, or SMS. All communication is done through official company emails and platforms.\nDouble-check email addresses. All communication from us will come from emails ending in @tether.to or @tether.io\nWe will never request payment or financial details. If someone asks for personal financial information or payment at any point during the hiring process, it is a scam. Please report it immediately.\n\nWhen in doubt, feel free to reach out through our official website."}
