{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2cface94b296c647","title":"Senior Product Designer (Full Remote - UAE)","company":"EverAI","location":"{\"city\":null,\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"UAE\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"UAE\",\"latitude\":0,\"longitude\":0,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"3 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2cface94b296c647","description":"Our Vision & Products\n\nEverAI — Building the Future of AI Companionship\n\nOne of the Top 15 Largest & Fastest-Growing AI Companies in the World\n\n40 Million Users in 2 years — Help Us Reach 100M first, 500M next\n\nAt EverAI, we’re shaping what it means to connect with AI. With 40 million users and counting, we're not just building products — we're creating entirely new categories.\n\nOur flagship product is the world’s largest AI girlfriend/boyfriend platform, redefining relationships for millions. It is governed by our proprietary moderation system, EverGuard — an internal AI designed to ensure everything we build is safe, ethical, and human-first.\n\nAnd we’re only just getting started!\n\nOur Team\n\nWe are an enthusiastic, passionate and hardworking team of 75 people. Our founding team has strong entrepreneurial experience building and scaling web products from 0 to IPO.\n\nAlexis Soulopoulos [CEO]\n\n• 10+ years in Tech Executive Leadership\n\n• Co-Founder Mad Paws Holdings (from 0 to IPO)\n\n• Forbes 30 under 30 + Deloitte TechFast50 ’22 & ‘23\n\nMichael Monin [Co-founder & CTO]\n\n• 10+ years as CTO / COO (web2/web3), 1+ year in AI/LLM\n\n• Serial-entrepreneur: MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) and Zipchat (AI Chatbot for E-commerce brands)\n\nThomas Lacroix [Co-founder & CMO]\n\n• 8+ years in Customer Acquisition & E-commerce Growth\n\n• Serial-entrepreneur: Curatible (sold to Blackstone) and MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue)\n\nMaruša Fasano [CFO/Legal]\n\n• 25+ years in Finance, Strategy, M&A\n\n• Ex-CFO/M&A @Curatible (exited to Blackstone)\n\n• Ex-President of the Board @SotremoSA (exited)\n\n• Co-founder/CFO @SoftOne (exited)\n\nYour Role\n\nWe’re looking for a Senior Product Designer to help shape the future of AI companionship. You’ll work across multiple areas of our product, from chat interfaces and AI content tools to payment flows, sign-up experiences, character creation, and marketing landing pages.\n\nYou’ll partner directly with our Product Design Lead to shape the future of AI companionship — defining design standards, refining systems, and delivering experiences that will be used and loved by millions. You’ll tackle problems few designers have ever faced, in a category that’s still being invented, and have the freedom to turn bold, AI‑powered ideas into elegant, high‑performing experiences.\n\nYour Responsibilities\nProduct & Feature Design\n\nOwn the end-to-end design process for features across multiple product areas from concept to delivery\n\nTranslate complex AI capabilities into clear, intuitive, and engaging user experiences\n\nMaintain and evolve a unified design system to ensure consistency and scalability across products\n\nDesign for emerging and evolving UX patterns in a fast‑moving AI product landscape, drawing on market trends and competitor insights\n\nAdapt quickly and manage multiple projects in parallel, delivering at speed without compromising quality\n\nCollaboration & Prototyping\n\nWork hand-in-hand with Product Managers, Engineers, and Marketers from concept to delivery\n\nRapidly prototype and test ideas before committing to full builds\n\nProvide clear, actionable feedback during design reviews and help raise the bar for design quality\n\nBe open to challenging ideas and having your own ideas challenged, fostering healthy debate to achieve the best design outcomes\n\nContinuous Improvement & Experimentation\n\nSupport fast-paced A/B testing with quick design iterations\n\nExperiment with AI-assisted design workflows to speed up delivery and explore new possibilities\n\nStay ahead of design trends, AI UX patterns, and emerging interaction models\n\nChallenges You’ll Tackle\n\nDesign for a product used by millions, ensuring high-quality experiences at scale\n\nWork across vastly different product surfaces while maintaining design consistency\n\nTranslate AI-powered capabilities into usable, engaging, and monetizable features\n\nImprove conversion and retention through iterative design and testing\n\nLead 0-to-1 feature design, from concept to launch, in ambiguous and fast-moving environments\n\nBalance creativity with data-driven decision-making to optimize user experience and business impact\n\nYour Qualifications\n\nMust-Haves\n\n5+ years of end-to-end product design experience, ideally in dating or social platforms, chat-based experiences, AI-generation tools, or live‑interactive gamified products\n\nStrong skills in interaction design, visual design, responsive design and information architecture\n\nProven ability to ship impactful features from 0 1 and iterate based on real-world feedback\n\nProficiency in Figma, with the ability to create production-ready UI assets\n\nExpert-level prototyping skills to clearly communicate ideas, flows, and interactions to developers and stakeholders\n\nResourceful problem-solving: able to find creative solutions that achieve both beauty and practicality.\n\nStrong ability to synthesise insights from competitor and market research into actionable design decisions\n\nNice‑to‑Haves\n\nExperience designing AI-driven products or other complex, emerging tech experiences\n\nExperience with AI content‑generation tools such as Midjourney, Kling, or Replicate\n\nA genuine interest in AI, demonstrated through personal projects, experimentation, or professional work\n\nStrong grasp of effective copywriting, recognising that copy is an integral part of design\n\nSkills in motion design, illustration, or 3D\n\nUnderstanding of HTML/CSS/JS for effective collaboration with developers to deliver solutions that are both visually compelling and technically sound\n\nExperience working on subscription‑based products with a focus on retention and monetization\n\nSoft Skills\n\nUser-obsessed: you start with the user and work backwards\n\nVelocity-driven: know when to go deep and when to ship fast\n\nCreative problem-solver: thrive in ambiguity and turn concepts into reality\n\nStrong communicator: articulate design rationale clearly to both designers and non-designers.\n\nCollaborative & humble: open to feedback and eager to share knowledge\n\n#NSFW: Comfortable building products based on uncensored models and content\n\nWhy EverAI?\n\nExponential Growth: From 40M users in 2 years, to 100M next — and 500M beyond\n\nTrack Record of Category-Creating Innovation: We consistently launch world-first AI applications — setting the pace, not following it\n\nGlobal Impact: Top-tier user growth, real-world adoption, and cultural relevance\n\nProven Leadership: A senior team that’s launched, scaled, and exited & IPO’d multiple scale ups — now fully focused on reshaping AI companionship\n\nElite Remote Team: 100% remote and built to win — world-class talent from Tier 1 tech companies, with a culture of ownership, velocity, and radical creativity\n\nEthical Core: Our AI ecosystem is governed by EverGuard, our proprietary AI moderation technology, ensuring responsible development at scale\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nContract Type: We prefer B2B, but we’re flexible, what matters is long-term commitment and impact\nWork From Anywhere: Fully remote. Choose the environment where you do your best work\nPaid Time Off: 4 weeks (20 working days) of PTO per year to recharge and reset\nAnnual Gathering: A yearly in-person meetup to connect, brainstorm, and celebrate wins together\nHealth & Wellness Support: Up to $200 per year for wellbeing expenses + unlimited 1:1 sessions with psychologists and lifestyle experts through OpenUp (also available for up to three family members)\nCo-Working Space Budget: Work from a co-working space up to twice per month (35 EUR / 40 USD per visit) to stay inspired and connected\nLearning Budget: Dedicated funds to support your professional growth: courses, books, conferences, events, or certifications\nEquipment: Company laptop provided + monitor budget up to $250 for your workspace setup\nAI Tools Access: Premium access to ChatGPT, Cursor, Hugging Face, and others, to power your ideas and workflows\n\nTop Tier Talent Is Our Multiplier\n\nWe’re a fully remote group of A-players from Tier 1 tech, led by an exec team who’ve launched, scaled, and exited multiple companies. We move fast, and care deeply about what we build — and who we build it with.\n\nWe’re looking for exceptional talent ready to ship & distribute world-first AI products at scale, fast, and co-create with us this category-defining business.\n\nIf that’s you — reach out and apply!\n\nExternal Referral Program\n\nKnow someone who could be a great fit for this role? You can refer them through the EverAI External Referral Program and earn a bonus of up to $2,500 if they’re hired. Submit a referral here."}
