{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=530ecce1caf37dae","title":"Zen Media Strategic Partnerships & Business Development Manager","company":"Optimum7","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"3 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=530ecce1caf37dae","description":"Strategic Partnerships & Business Development Manager - MENA\n\nLocation: Remote, Dubai\n\nExperience Required: Minimum 5 years in business development, partnerships, channel sales, or strategic networking roles\n\nZen Media is the go-to B2B marketing and PR agency helping enterprise software, healthcare technology, professional services, and manufacturing brands achieve measurable growth and market leadership. By combining strategic content, leveraged media relations, and dynamic social amplification, we help our clients influence discerning buyers, shorten sales cycles, and drive ROI. Our work has been featured in leading publications such as Forbes, Fast Company, Ad Age, and The Wall Street Journal, and we have helped clients double their industry dominance and achieve profitable exits.\n\nRole Overview:\n\nWe are seeking a results-focused Strategic Partnerships & Business Development Manager (MENA) to build and strengthen Zen Media’’s partner ecosystem across the Middle East. This individual will identify, engage, and secure high-value partnerships with digital agencies, technology providers, B2B solution companies, consultants, and enterprise networks that can generate qualified opportunities and mutual growth.\n\nThis is a highly network-driven role, ideal for someone who excels in relationship building, communicates charismatically and professionally, and understands how to implement partnership strategies that lead to measurable revenue impact.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nDevelop and execute partnership and business development strategies across the MENA region in alignment with company growth goals.\n\nBuild a strong pipeline of partnerships with agencies, SaaS companies, enterprise solution providers, technology platforms, and professional networks.\n\nProactively conduct networking, outreach, and relationship-building through events, associations, digital channels, and industry communities.\n\nRepresent Zen Media in the market as a knowledgeable, credible, and relationship-first growth partner.\n\nLead the full partnership lifecycle—prospecting, pitch, negotiation, onboarding, activation, and ongoing collaboration.\n\nMaintain timely and structured follow-up schedules to maximize alliance engagement and conversion.\n\nWork closely with marketing, sales, and executive leadership to develop joint strategies for co-marketing, lead sharing, and shared revenue models.\n\nTrack performance metrics, including partnership pipeline growth, conversions, revenue contribution, and engagement results.\n\nKeep an active pulse on the MENA market, competitive landscape, and opportunities for expansion.\n\nDeliver regular reporting and insights to internal leadership for strategic decision-making.\n\nWhat You Bring\n\nMinimum 5+ years of experience in business development, alliance management, channel sales, or partnership growth roles.\n\nStrong network-building abilities and proven experience developing strategic relationships in the MENA region.\n\nExceptional communication and stakeholder management skills—written, verbal, presentation, and negotiation.\n\nConfident and professional presence in events, meetings, networking settings, and digital interactions.\n\nTarget-driven mindset with the ability to independently manage pipelines, timelines, and objectives.\n\nExperience in B2B, digital marketing, SaaS, eCommerce, or related industries is a strong advantage.\n\nAbility to work