{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=abddf5a1ab3bc16e","title":"Senior Product Manager - Marketplace Health","company":"Careem","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"2 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=abddf5a1ab3bc16e","description":"Careem is building the Everything App for the greater Middle East — making it easy to move around, order food and groceries, manage payments, and more. Our purpose is simple: to simplify and improve people’s lives and build an awesome organisation that inspires.\nSince 2012, Careem has enabled earnings for over 2.5 million Captains, simplified the lives of more than 70 million customers, and built a platform where the region’s best talent and entrepreneurs thrive. We operate in 70+ cities across 10 countries, from Morocco to Pakistan.\n\nWe’re now entering our next chapter — one powered by AI. We’re looking for AI talent: curious problem-solvers who know how to apply AI to build tools, automate workflows, and create real impact. Whether it’s streamlining operations, enhancing customer experience, or reimagining internal systems — we want people who can make Careem work smarter and move faster.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nThe Senior Product Manager will lead the Marketplace Health Squad, responsible for shaping demand and supply dynamics across Careem’s platform. The role focuses on ensuring marketplace balance, operational efficiency, and growth across verticals (Food, Quik, Mobility). The ideal candidate combines deep data fluency, technical rigor, and commercial acumen to design scalable solutions that optimize the core marketplace engine.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nMarketplace Health & Efficiency: Own the health of the supply-demand ecosystem — continuously monitor and improve metrics like fulfillment rate, cancellations, idle supply, and order wait times.\n\nIdentify and execute levers to dynamically balance demand and supply through pricing, incentives, batching, and allocation algorithms.\n\nPartner with analytics and data science teams to develop forecasting, elasticity modeling, and market simulation tools.\n\nDemand & Supply Shaping: Build frameworks for demand stimulation (e.g., promos, pricing) and supply activation (e.g., shift planning, guarantees).\n\nCollaborate with vertical teams to ensure marketplace strategies align with business and experience goals.\n\nDrive initiatives that improve captain utilization, order per hour (OPH), and customer conversion rates.\n\nExperimentation & Data Science Integration: Design and run A/B experiments to validate hypotheses across incentive, pricing, and routing domains.\n\nTranslate complex analytical insights into actionable product strategy; partner closely with Data Science to embed models into real-time systems.\n\nLeverage ML-driven approaches for prediction, dynamic decisioning, and optimization at scale.\n\nCross-Functional Leadership: Align product, engineering, analytics, and operations around a unified Marketplace Health roadmap.\n\nRepresent marketplace trade-offs in leadership discussions, balancing growth, customer experience, and profitability.\n\nFoster a culture of experimentation, transparency, and impact measurement within the squad.\n\nWhat You’ll Bring\n\nBachelor’s degree in Engineering, Computer Science, Economics, or a related quantitative field (MBA preferred).\n\n6–9 years of experience in Product Management, ideally in E-commerce, Ride-hailing, or Quick Commerce.\n\nProven experience in marketplace optimization, dynamic pricing, or incentive systems.\n\nStrong exposure to working with Data Science and Engineering teams — comfort with metrics, experimentation, and model-based products.\n\nExperience managing high-scale, real-time systems and driving measurable outcomes in ambiguous, high-growth environments.\n\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills with ability to interpret complex data into actionable decisions.\n\nFamiliarity with SQL, experimentation platforms, and data visualization tools (Looker, Tableau, etc.).\n\nExceptional communication, stakeholder management, and execution ownership.\n\nBias for action, outcome-oriented, and thrives in a fast-paced cross-functional setup.\n\nWhat we’ll provide you\n\nWe offer colleagues the opportunity to drive impact in the region while they learn and grow. As a full time Careem colleague, you will be able to:\n\nWork and learn from great minds by joining a community of inspiring colleagues.\nPut your passion to work in a purposeful organisation dedicated to creating impact in a region with a lot of untapped potential.\nExplore new opportunities to learn and grow every day.\nWork 4 days a week in office & 1 day from home, and remotely from any country in the world for 30 days a year with unlimited vacation days per year. (If you are in an individual contributor role in tech, you will have 2 office days a week and 3 to work from home.)\nAccess to healthcare benefits and fitness reimbursements for health activities including gym, health club, and training classes."}
