mation, lead qualification, CRM updates)\n• AI Customer Service Agents (ticket triage, response drafting, sentiment analysis)\n• AI Recruitment Agents (CV screening, candidate scoring, AI interviewers)\n• AI Executive Insight Agents (KPI summaries, reporting automation)\n\nExperience required in:\n\n• Multi-agent systems\n• Tool / function calling\n• Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)\n• Memory systems and vector databases\n• Workflow orchestration for AI agents\n\nLLM & Model Experience\n\nHands-on experience with:\n\n• OpenAI ecosystem (production or prototype deployments)\n• Anthropic Claude\n• Google Gemini\n• Azure OpenAI\n• Open-source LLMs (Llama, Mistral or similar)\n• Structured outputs and guardrails\n• Model selection based on use case, latency and cost\n\nCRM & System Integrations\n\nExperience integrating AI systems with:\n\n• Salesforce (preferred but not essential)\n• Microsoft Dynamics\n• HubSpot\n• Zoho\n\nUnderstanding of:\n\n• REST APIs\n• OAuth authentication\n• Webhooks\n• Automation tools (Make, Zapier, n8n or similar)\n\nSalesforce CRM experience is preferred but not essential.\n\nAI Data & Knowledge Architecture\n\nExperience with:\n\n• Vector databases (Pinecone, Weaviate, Chroma or similar)\n• Knowledge retrieval systems\n• Semantic data structuring\n• Business data modelling for AI use cases\n\nConversational & Voice AI\n\nExperience with:\n\n• Conversational AI frameworks\n• AI voice agents\n• Speech-to-text and text-to-speech systems\n• Telephony or real-time AI integrations\n\nGovernance & Responsible AI\n\nKnowledge of:\n\n• Data governance principles\n• Prompt injection mitigation\n• AI monitoring and evaluation\n• Responsible AI deployment\n\nCandidate Requirements\n\n• 12–24 months hands-on experience building AI agents or AI automation systems\n• Proven working prototype examples of AI agents already built and deployed (must be able to demonstrate)\n• Strong systems-thinking and architecture mindset\n• Comfortable operating in a fast-moving innovation environment\n• Commercial awareness and ability to translate technical solutions into business outcomes\n\nThis role is suited to a builder who has already created real AI agents and wants to scale that experience into enterprise-grade deployments.\n\nWhat You Will Help Build\n\n• A full AI Agent Ecosystem\n• A catalogue of modular AI automation solutions\n• Enterprise-ready AI deployment frameworks\n• AI training and enablement programmes\n\nIf you have already built AI agents and want to help architect and scale a dedicated AI Labs division, we would like to hear from you.\n\nPlease apply with:\n\n• Your LinkedIn profile\n• A short summary of AI agents you have built\n• Links, demos or documentation of prototype systems\n\nIf you’d like, I can now:\n\n• Make a shorter recruiter-friendly LinkedIn ad version\n• Add compensation band positioning\n• Write a direct message template to attract candidates\n• Or structure an interview scoring framework for this role\n\nWhat stage are you at — posting publicly or targeting specific profiles?"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d18e020d3976fd56","title":"Deployment Strategist","company":"","location":"{\"city\":null,\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"UAE\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"UAE\",\"latitude\":0,\"longitude\":0,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"3 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d18e020d3976fd56","description":"Deployment Strategist\n\nLocation: Global / Remote-First / Hybrid\n\nType: Full-time\n\nAbout Aurem\n\nAurem is building the AI-native operating system for the global retirement and wealth industry — a $58.5 trillion market still running on legacy, pre-internet infrastructure. We unify complex products, processes, and data into a single intelligent platform. Our current and future clients span the world’s largest banks, insurers, pension providers, and governments.\n\nThe role: Deployment strategist\n\nAt Aurem, Deployment Strategists are the tip of the spear — driving strategic implementations, shaping products with clients, and turning vision into working systems. You’ll partner with some of the world’s most complex financial institutions to reimagine how they deliver retirement and wealth products at scale.\n\nYou won’t just manage projects — you’ll lead transformation from the ground up. You’ll uncover deep user needs, structure ambiguous problems, and orchestrate the deployment of Aurem’s platform to create immediate and lasting impact.\n\nWhat’s your playground\n\nThe Deployment Strategist sits at the center of Aurem’s delivery operating model, working across a tightly coordinated team including:\n\nForward Deployed Engineers (FDEs): Technical leads focused on client-side integrations and implementations\n\nPlatform Operations Managers: Internal enablers who ensure delivery systems, environments, and tooling are ready and aligned\n\nBusiness Operations Managers: Owners of compliance, end-user onboarding, and customer support infrastructure, processes and procedures.\n\nIn this structure, Deployment Strategists own the delivery outcome — from scoping to go-live. They are accountable for aligning all functions around a clear roadmap, managing external stakeholders, owning change delivery, and translating complexity into scalable action.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nLead strategic deployments from scoping to go-live — engaging directly with client execs, product teams, and operations leaders\n\nShape product from the field, working with engineering and design to tailor Aurem’s platform to complex client workflows\n\nDefine success by deeply understanding the business, regulatory, and operational constraints of clients across retirement, wealth, and insurance\n\nDrive change by designing modular rollout strategies that minimize risk, accelerate time to value, and scale impact over time\n\nOperate as a partner, not a vendor — challenging client thinking, unblocking complexity, and aligning stakeholders around a new way of operating\n\nWhat You Bring\n\n5–10+ years experience in consulting, strategy, fintech, or enterprise deployment in a high-stakes environment\n\nDeep analytical and first-principles problem-solving skills\n\nExceptional communication and stakeholder management, from C-suite to operations floor\n\nComfort navigating ambiguity, complexity, and rapid scale\n\nAn instinct for systems thinking, user needs, and product design\n\nExperience with financial services — especially retirement, wealth, or insurance — is a strong advantage\n\nExpected Outcomes\n\nDeliver client onboarding and deployment plans that are tightly scoped, on time, and aligned with measurable success criteria\n\nEnsure cross-functional coordination across internal teams (Platform Ops, FDEs, Biz Ops) and client stakeholders\n\nTranslate business requirements into actionable product inputs and support agile iteration throughout implementation\n\nDesign and own repeatable delivery playbooks, standardizing rituals like kickoffs, RAG tracking, and change control\n\nLead structured change management processes, including the intake, prioritization, and delivery of change requests in close alignment with client and internal teams\n\nBe recognized by clients as a trusted partner, not just a delivery lead — able to unblock complexity, drive decisions, and influence outcomes at multiple levels\n\nWhy This Role Matters\n\nAurem is not a vendor. We’re a partner in transformation. Deployment Strategists are central to this — embedding within client teams, building conviction, and ensuring we don’t just deploy software, but deliver change.\n\nYou’ll work alongside engineers, product thinkers, and operators who care deeply about transforming how the world saves and invests. You’ll have the freedom to move fast, the mandate to think big, and the platform to make it real.\n\nWe win by helping our clients win. If you’re ready to lead that charge — let’s talk."}
