{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4380199451","title":"Commercial Marketing Manager - 1 year Contract","company":"Tahaluf","location":"Riyadh","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"Tahaluf is the largest B2B live and on-demand events organiser in Saudi Arabia by space, attendance, colleagues, and revenue. It is a joint venture between Informa PLC, the Saudi Federation for Cybersecurity, Programming and Drones (SAFCSP), and the Events Investment Fund (EIF).Tahaluf is bold, visionary, and determined to make an impact. Our team fosters a culture of collaboration, creativity, and a little fun, here teamwork rules and work feels as exciting as the events we create. Scaling at this pace also requires exceptional local partners, and Tahaluf is proud to work with a range of government and non-government organisations at the forefront of Saudi Arabia’s B2B and B2C large-scale events scene.Be part of something BIG with Tahaluf’s series of record-breaking events: LEAP and Cityscape - the largest events in the world in their respective fields of tech and real estate; Black Hat MEA - a Guinness World Record holder for the largest CTF competition during the event; and CPHI Middle East - the largest pharma debut event in history, to name just a few. Tahaluf is making a huge impact on the global events sector.Join our ambitious and highly committed team, unafraid to push boundaries and disrupt the status quo. From day one, you’ll dive into large-scale projects under the guidance of a supportive leadership team that will encourage your personal development and open doors to new opportunities.Job DescriptionWe’re hiring a commercially driven, insight-led Commercial Marketing Manager (Contractor) to support the execution of high-performing campaigns across a portfolio of global B2B events. You’ll work across cybersecurity, fintech, and tech, helping us generate high-quality leads, support sales conversion, and hit ambitious revenue targets.This is a contract-based, remote or Riyadh-based role, ideal for a self-sufficient marketing expert who’s confident in owning campaign delivery and using data to steer performance.🔹 What You'll DeliverWithin your first 12 months, you’ll:Deliver marketing campaigns on time, within deadline and at a consistently high standard.Support the marketing team to contribute 5-15% of total revenue (event-depending) through MQL generation and nurture.Use our tech stack to build automations, segment data, and report insights that highlight what’s working (and what isn’t).🔹 ResponsibilitiesLead on the execution of multi-channel campaigns (email, content, digital, automation).Build audience segments and automations in CRM (Salesforce, Eloqua, or equivalent).Collaborate with the brand, attendee marketing, and sales teams to align marketing activity with pipeline goals.Report on campaign performance and provide insight-based recommendations for optimisation.Apply AI tools (like ChatGPT) to speed up content production and streamline repetitive tasks.Identify trends and opportunities for repurposing campaign assets across the portfolio.Support development of future marketing strategies based on campaign analysis and commercial performance.Qualifications Bachelors Degree🔹 What We’re Looking ForProven B2B marketing experience (events, SaaS, or demand generation preferred).Expert-level experience with CRM systems and marketing automation, platform flexible but you must understand the fundamentals (segmentation, lead scoring, nurture flows).Data-savvy and insight-driven, you track what’s working and aren’t afraid to pivot.Hands-on campaign executor who’s comfortable working in a fast-paced, deadline-driven team.Confident in copywriting, building emails, and planning out campaign timelines.Collaborative and curious, someone who actively spots ways to improve cross-team workflows.AI-aware, you know how to use ChatGPT and other AI tools to improve productivity and output.🔹 Optional but Nice to HaveExperience working with Eloqua, Salesforce, Airtable, or similar toolsPrior experience in the Middle East or KSA marketsExposure to paid media strategy or briefingFintech, cybersecurity, or tech industry knowledge (not required)Additional InformationWe work hard to make sure life at Tahaluf is rewarding, supportive and enjoyable for everyone. We’re not solely focused on a checklist of skills. We champion energy and ambition and look for colleagues who will roll their sleeves up, join in and help make things happen. We don't just accept difference, we celebrate it.  We welcome applicants from all backgrounds and circumstances and base hiring decisions on relevant qualifications and merit.  We are proud to provide a disability-friendly environment. If you require any support or adjustments to participate in our interview or selection processes, please let us know."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4374878600","title":"Customer Success Manager SaaS B2B remote","company":"Propulse","location":"France","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"Prière de ne pas postuler si vous n'avez pas déjà évolué dans le secteur SaaS B2B pendant au moins 3 ans en tant que Customer Success Manager.Propulse est le leader français de la croissance en automatique sur Instagram. Nous aidons les entreprises à développer leur audience Instagram et à générer plus d’opportunités business grâce à une technologie d’automatisation intelligente, connectée à leur compte.Notre secret ? Un produit qui automatise les interactions ciblées avec les audiences les plus susceptibles d’être intéressées, et un positionnement 100% orienté performance.👉 Après avoir doublé notre MRR sur les 9 derniers mois et atteint 1,5M€ d’ARR (SLG et bootstrap), nous cherchons un(e) Customer Success Manager (Profil Builder) pour structurer notre pôle CS de A à Z. Ton but : consolider cette croissance en transformant nos utilisateurs en clients ultra-engagés et en maximisant notre Net Retention Rate (NRR).🎯 Ta missionAssurer la réussite client sur l’intégralité du cycle de vie (onboarding → adoption → valeur → rétention → expansion). Tu ne seras pas un agent de support glorifié, mais un véritable Trusted Advisor. Ta mission est d'industrialiser l’accompagnement (Tech-Touch / Low-Touch) pour scaler le pôle, d'encadrer le support existant, de réduire drastiquement le churn, et d'être la Voix du Client (VoC) en interne pour guider notre roadmap Produit vers ce qui a un réel impact business.🛠 Tes responsabilitésL'immersion (Mois 1) : Mettre les mains dans le cambouis. Tu feras du support (Intercom) en binôme avec notre agent support actuel pour maîtriser parfaitement le produit, les cas d'usage et la réalité du terrain.Management &amp; Structuration (Mois 2+) : Tu prendras le lead sur notre agent de support. Ton rôle : le manager, le faire monter en compétence, et outiller son quotidien (Knowledge Base, macros) pour te libérer du temps et te concentrer à 100% sur le Success stratégique.Structurer l'Onboarding : Créer un parcours Tech-Touch automatisé pour rendre les clients autonomes, avec un time-to-value express (Aha moment &lt; 24h).Prévention du Churn : Mettre en place un Health Score fiable et piloter une routine d'alerte. Déployer un process \"Renew M-3\" pour anticiper les renouvellements bien avant la date fatidique.Expansion &amp; ROI : Identifier les opportunités d’upsell/cross-sell (Instagram, TikTok), mener des QBRs (Quarterly Business Reviews) orientées résultats, et faire la passe décisive aux Sales.Alignement interne : Gérer la passation Sales ➔ CSM sans friction. Collecter la VoC et collaborer avec le CEO, le Produit et le Growth pour s'assurer que les demandes fortes trouvent des solutions scalables.🧠 Profil recherchéExpérience : Min. 3 ans en Customer Success B2B SaaS. Tu as déjà structuré des process de zéro dans un environnement en forte croissance.Compétences techniques (Hard Skills) :Maîtrise de la data SaaS (MRR, NRR, GRR, Cohortes, Churn drivers).Capacité à créer des playbooks, des automatisations lifecycle et une Knowledge Base efficace.À l'aise avec les outils CS (CRM, Intercom, Looker, Notion).Qualités humaines (Soft Skills) :Leadership &amp; Management : Tu sais encadrer, déléguer et faire grandir une personne sous ta responsabilité (notre agent support actuel).Courage managérial : Tu sais dire \"non\" à un client, challenger ses demandes et argumenter ta position. Tu n'es pas un \"people pleaser\".Posture de Consultant : Tu écoutes à 80% et tu parles à 20% (Discovery). Tu ramènes systématiquement la discussion au ROI et aux objectifs business du client, pas au bavardage.Ownership : Autonome, tu ne subis pas le quotidien. Tu anticipes les risques, tu prends les sujets, tu boucles et tu capitalises. Calme sous la pression.📐 KPIs sur lesquels tu seras attendu(e)Net Retention Rate (NRR) &amp; Gross Retention Rate (GRR)Churn rate (Logo + Revenu) : Objectif &lt; 7%Time-to-Value : % de clients activés sous 24hGénération d'opportunités d'Upsell / Cross-sellDéploiement effectif des process CS (Health Score, Playbooks, Parcours automatisé)🎁 Ce qu’on t’offrePoste en full remote, flexible.L'opportunité de créer un pôle CS from scratch et d'avoir un impact direct sur le produit.Collaboration directe avec Enguerrand (CEO).Un produit qui performe, avec une base clients solide (1000+ clients actifs).Une culture de la transparence, du test &amp; learn et de la liberté.CDI ou freelance, selon ton profil.🔍 Processus de recrutementQuestionnaire + CVVidéo asyncEntretien avec Enguerrand (CEO)Business case concret (Mise en situation Client / Analyse de Churn)Second entretien avec Enguerrand &amp; l'équipeOnboarding express 🚀🔢 Propulse, en bref+1000 clients actifs1,5M€ d’ARRCréé en 201715 collaborateurs100% de croissance en 2025Moyenne d’âge : 35 ans👉 Si tu as l'âme d'un(e) \"Builder\", que tu aimes l'impact direct et que tu sais allier empathie client et fermeté business, c’est ici que ça se passe. On n'attend plus que toi 🦾"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4379473271","title":"Customer Support Specialist","company":"Orange Logic","location":"Irvine","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"At Orange Logic, we’ve been solving complex content challenges for over two decades—driven by innovation, curiosity, and a passion for impact, our intelligent Digital Asset Management (DAM) system, Orange Logic Platform, empowers organizations across industries to manage, access, and leverage their digital assets more effectively. We’re not just building powerful software—we’re building a team of bold thinkers, collaborators, and problem-solvers who care deeply about delivering real value. The Customer Support Specialist serves as both a technical consultant and support expert, partnering closely with clients to understand their unique use cases and help them get the most out of the Orange Logic platform. This role is equal parts trusted consultant, problem-solver, client advocate, and technical guide—helping clients navigate challenges, optimize workflows, and maximize value from our solutions.You Role at Orange Logic:Serve as a primary point of contact and trusted consultant for clients seeking assistance with software issues, usage questions, or system optimization.Diagnose, troubleshoot, and resolve software-related challenges in client environments, escalating complex issues as needed.Deliver white-glove support, building trust and confidence with clients by providing accurate, helpful, and timely solutions.Conduct proactive client outreach to ensure satisfaction, adoption, and engagement with new features or workflows.Partner with clients to translate business needs into technical workflows, offering best-practice recommendations.Document client interactions, solutions, and product feedback for use in knowledge bases and internal product discussions.Identify and advocate for enhancements and usability improvements based on recurring client pain points or feedback.Colla